<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="339" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1364,1643]" pageId="5" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1364,1390]" pageId="5" pageNumber="339">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="Grimaldi, D." box="[439,614,1364,1390]" pageId="5" pageNumber="339" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref8110" refString="Grimaldi, D. (1993) Amber Fossil Drosophilidae (Diptera), Part II: Review of the genus Hyalistata, New status (Steganinae). American Museum Novitates, 10024 (3084), 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1993">Grimaldi, 1993</bibRefCitation>
). General body color slightly dark to light yellow; arista micropubescent; wing hyaline; proclinate fronto-orbital seta slightly smaller than anterior reclinate fronto-orbital seta; one postpronotal seta and 6–7 postpronotal setulae; tergites with a varied pattern of spots (
<tableCitation box="[1036,1120,1436,1462]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="TABLE 1. Distinguishing abdominal tergite coloration characters between species of Hyalistata." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/90F115ECC204FFA8C4F4D6C0FB217C98" pageId="5" pageNumber="339" tableUuid="90F115ECC204FFA8C4F4D6C0FB217C98">Table 1</tableCitation>
), ventral lobe of epandrium with 12–15 fine setulae, all with large sockets; cercus with numerous short, fine setulae (no distinctively large setae). A pair of postgonites with apical comb-like row of 8–14 long, heavily sclerotized peg-prensisetae. Pregonites as rounded lobes, largely fused to hypandrium, with 4–12 fine setulae. Phallus indistinguishable or distiphallus large, bulbous, sometimes with a pair of small, lightly sclerotized flanges. Hypandrium with a narrow base, distinctively Y-shaped or asymmetrical, often bent (except for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wheeler" authorityYear="1960" box="[706,820,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hyalistata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="339" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[706,820,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="339">H. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
